ZH: 我的铅笔已经用完了。
EN: My pencil is already worn down.

ZH: 铅是一种有毒金属。
EN: Lead is a toxic metal.

ZH: 请把这支铅笔给我。
EN: Please pass me this pencil.

ZH: 这块铅板很重。
EN: This lead plate is very heavy.

ZH: 铅的熔点比较低。
EN: Lead has a relatively low melting point.

ZH: 我们要做实验，需要用到一些铅。
EN: We need to use some lead for the experiment.

ZH: 这个机关铅制的雕塑非常精美。
EN: This mechanical lead sculpture is very exquisite.

ZH: 我家门前的铅球被偷走了。
EN: The lead ball in front of my house was stolen.

ZH: 那条船在沉没时释放出了许多铅。
EN: The sinking ship released a lot of lead.

ZH: 这家公司因为铅污染被罚款了。
EN: This company was fined for lead pollution.

ZH: 你能告诉我铅的密度是多少吗？
EN: Can you tell me what the density of lead is?

ZH: 在古代，铅被用来制作铅字、铅华等。
EN: In ancient times, lead was used to make lead type, lead powder and so on.

ZH: 铅在古埃及被用作眼部化妆品。
EN: Lead was used as eye makeup in ancient Egypt.

ZH: 铅盐可用来检测硫化氢。
EN: Lead salts can be used to detect hydrogen sulphide.

ZH: 这片土地受到了铅污染。
EN: This land has been contaminated with lead.

ZH: 铅笔在中文中又称为铅嘴。
EN: Pencils are also known as lead mouths in Chinese.

ZH: 请勿将铅与食物一同储放。
EN: Please do not store lead with food.

ZH: 这个铅质的假火枪在舞台上看起来很逼真。
EN: This lead fake gun looks very realistic on stage.

ZH: 铅笔芯的外层通常由木材包裹。
EN: The outer layer of a pencil lead is usually wrapped in wood.

ZH: 铅和其它金属结合，可制得许多耐蚀合金。
EN: Lead combined with other metals can make many corrosion-resistant alloys.
